#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:1
msgid "Coding Conventions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:3
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:5
msgid ""
"VTK is a large body of code with many users and developers. Coding in a "
"consistent style eases shared development. VTK's style guidelines also "
"ensure wide portability. All code that is contributed to VTK must conform to "
"the following style guidelines. Exceptions are permissible, following "
"discussion in code review, as long as the result passes the nightly "
"regression tests. External code contributed into the ThirdParty directory is "
"exempt from most of the following rules except for the rules that say \"All "
"code\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:14
msgid ""
"All code that is compiled into VTK by default must be compatible with VTK's "
"BSD- style license."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:15
msgid ""
"Copyright notices should appear at the top of C++ header and implementation "
"files using SPDX syntax."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:16
msgid "All C++ code must be valid C++17 code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:18
msgid "Multiple inheritance is not allowed in VTK classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:20
msgid "Rationale: One important reason is that Java does not support it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:21
msgid ""
"Only one public class per header file. Internal helper classes may be "
"forward declared in header files, but can then only be defined in "
"implementation files, ie using the PIMPL idiom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:23
msgid ""
"Rationale: helpful when searching the code and limits header inclusion bloat "
"that slows compilation time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:25
msgid "Class names and file names must match, class names must be unique."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:27
msgid ""
"Rationale: helpful when searching the code, includes are flattened at "
"install."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:29
msgid ""
"The indentation style used is a modified version of the [Allman style]"
"(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indent_style#Allman_style). Indentations "
"consist of two spaces, and tabs are not permitted. Additionally, trailing "
"whitespace is not allowed. Curly braces, which serve as scope delimiters, "
"are placed on the line following the control statement and are indented to "
"the same level as that statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:31
msgid ""
"Rationale: Readability and historical, Removing tabs ensures that blocks are "
"indented consistently in all editors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:33
msgid ""
"Conditional clauses (including loop conditionals such as for and while) must "
"be in braces below the conditional. Ie, instead of `if (test) clause` or `if "
"(test) { clause }`, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:35
msgid ""
"if (test)\n"
"{\n"
"  clause\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:41
msgid "Rationale: helpful when running code through a debugger"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:43
msgid ""
"Init-statement in a condition like `if ( int i = 0; ... )` is  allowed "
"except for modifying an existing variable outside the conditional clause.   "
"Rationale: Readability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:46
msgid ""
"Only alphanumeric characters in names. Use capitalization to demarcate words "
"within a name (i.e., camel case). Use pascal case for `static` variables. "
"Preprocessor variables are the exception, and should be in all caps with a "
"single underscore to demarcate words."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:48
#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:60
#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:162
#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:166
msgid "Rationale: Readability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:50
msgid ""
"Every class, macro, etc starts with either vtk or VTK. Classes should all "
"start with lowercase vtk and macros or constants can start with either."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:52
msgid "Rationale: avoids name clashes with other libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:54
msgid "Every free function should be in the \"vtk\" namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:56
msgid "Rationale: Namespace symbol collision avoidance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:58
msgid ""
"After the `vtk` prefix, capitalize the first letter of class names, methods "
"and static and instance variables. Local variables are allowed to vary, but "
"ideally should start in lower case and then proceed in camel case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:62
msgid ""
"Try to always spell out a name and not use abbreviations except in cases "
"where the shortened form is obvious and widely understood."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:64
msgid "Rationale: Readability, self-documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:66
msgid ""
"Classes that derive from `vtkObject` should have protected constructors and "
"destructors, and privately declared but unimplemented copy constructor and "
"assignment operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:68
msgid ""
"Classes that don't derive from `vtkObject` should obey the rule of three. If "
"the class implements the destructor, copy constructor or copy assignment "
"operator they should implement all of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:70
msgid ""
"Rationale: VTK's reference counting implementation depends on carefully "
"controlling each object's lifetime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:72
msgid ""
"Following the copyright notice, the name and purpose of each class should be "
"documented at the top of the header with standard doxygen markup.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:73
msgid ""
"/**\n"
" * @class vtkclassname\n"
" * @brief one line description\n"
" *\n"
" * Longer description of class here.\n"
"*/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:82
msgid ""
"Rationale: Doxygen generated documentation uses this to describe each class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:84
msgid "Public methods must be documented with doxygen markup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:85
msgid ""
"/**\n"
" * Explanation of what the method/ivar is for\n"
" */\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:90
msgid ""
"Descriptions should do more than simply restate the method or ivar's name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:92
msgid ""
"The documentation for each public ivar should document the default value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:94
msgid ""
"The documentation style for SetGet macros should be a single comment for the "
"pair and a brief description of the variable that is being set/get. Use "
"doxygen group marking to make the comment apply to both macro expanded "
"functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:96
msgid ""
"///@{\n"
"/**\n"
" * Set / get the sharpness of decay of the splats.\n"
" * This is the exponent constant in the Gaussian\n"
" * equation. Normally this is a negative value.\n"
" */\n"
" */\n"
"vtkSetMacro(ExponentFactor,double);\n"
"vtkGetMacro(ExponentFactor,double);\n"
"///@}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:109
msgid ""
"The documentation style for vector macros is to name each of the resulting "
"variables. For example comment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:110
msgid ""
"/**\n"
" * Set/Get the color which is used to draw shapes in the image. The "
"parameters are SetDrawColor(red, green, blue, alpha)\n"
" */\n"
"vtkSetVector4Macro(DrawColor, double);\n"
"vtkGetVector4Macro(DrawColor, double);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:118
msgid ""
"The description for SetClamp macros must describe the valid range of values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:119
msgid ""
"/**\n"
" * Should the data with value 0 be ignored? Valid range (0, 1).\n"
" */\n"
"vtkSetClampMacro(IgnoreZero, int, 0, 1);\n"
"vtkGetMacro(IgnoreZero, int);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:127
msgid ""
"Rationale: Doxygen generated documentation (http://www.vtk.org/doc/nightly/"
"html/) is generated from these comments and should be consistently readable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:129
msgid ""
"Public and even Protected instance variables are allowed only in exceptional "
"situations. Private variables should be used instead with public access "
"given via Set/Get macro methods when needed. Rationale: Consistent API, ease "
"of deprecation, and SetMacro takes part in reference counting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:132
msgid ""
"Protected methods are allowed only when they are intended to be used by "
"inheriting classes and overridden by inheriting classes. Private methods "
"should be the default for any method. Please note this is not true in many "
"classes but should be followed when adding new code. Rationale: Consistent "
"API, ease of deprecation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:136
msgid ""
"Accessors to `vtkObject` instance variables should be declared in the header "
"file, and defined in the implementation file with the vtkCxxSetObjectMacro. "
"Rationale: Reduces header file bloat and assists in reference counting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:139
msgid ""
"Use `this->` inside of methods to access class methods and instance "
"variables. Rationale: Readability as it helps to distinguish local variables "
"from instance variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:142
msgid ""
"Header files should normally have just two includes, one for the superclass' "
"header file and one for the class' module export header declaration. It is "
"required that all but the superclass header have a comment explaining why "
"the extra includes are necessary. Care should be taken to minimize the "
"number of includes in public headers, with predeclaration/PIMPL preferred. "
"Rationale: limits header inclusion bloat that slows compilation time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:145
msgid ""
"Include statements in implementation files should generally be in "
"alphabetical order, grouped by type. For example, VTK includes first, system "
"includes, STL includes, and Qt includes. Rationale: avoid redundant "
"includes, and keep a logical order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:148
msgid ""
"All subclasses of `vtkObject` should include a `PrintSelf()` method that "
"prints all publicly accessible ivars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:150
msgid ""
"Rationale: useful in debugging and in wrapped languages that lack sufficient "
"introspection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:151
msgid ""
"All subclasses of `vtkObject` should include a type macro in their class "
"declaration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:153
msgid ""
"Rationale: VTK's implementation of runtime type information depends on it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:154
msgid ""
"Do not use `id` as a variable name in public headers, also avoid `min`, "
"`max`, and other symbols that conflict with the Windows API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:156
msgid ""
"Rationale: `id` is a reserved word in Objective-C++, and against variable "
"name rules. `min`, `max`, and less common identifiers listed in Testing/Core/"
"WindowsMangleList.py are declared in the Windows API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:158
msgid ""
"Prefer the use of vtkNew when the variable would be classically treated as a "
"stack variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:160
msgid ""
"Eighty character line width is preferred. More than one hundred is not "
"allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:164
msgid ""
"Method definitions in implementation files should be preceded by // followed "
"by 78 `-` characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:168
msgid ""
"New code must include regression tests that will run on the dashboards. The "
"name of the file to test vtkClassName should be TestClassName.cxx. Each test "
"should call several functions, each as short as possible, to exercise a "
"specific functionality of the class. The `main()` function of the test file "
"must be called TestClassName(int, char*[])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:170
msgid "Rationale: Code that is not tested can not be said to be working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:172
msgid ""
"All code must compile and run without warning or error messages on the "
"nightly dashboards, which include Windows, Mac, Linux and Unix machines. "
"Exceptions can be made, for example to exclude warnings from ThirdParty "
"libraries, by adding exceptions to CMake/CTestCustom.cmake.in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:174
msgid ""
"Namespaces should not be brought into global scope in any public headers, i."
"e. the `using` keyword should not appear in any public headers except within "
"class scope. It can be used in implementations, but it is preferred to bring "
"symbols into the global scope rather than an entire namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:176
msgid ""
"Rationale: Using VTK API should not have side-effects where parts of the std "
"namespace (or the entire thing) are suddenly moved to global scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:178
msgid ""
"While much of the legacy VTK API uses integers for boolean values, new "
"interfaces should prefer the bool type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:180
#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:209
msgid "Rationale: Readability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:182
msgid ""
"Template classes are permitted, but must be excluded from wrapped languages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:184
msgid ""
"Rationale: The concept of templates doesn't exist in all wrapped languages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:186
msgid "Prefer overloading functions to default arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:188
msgid ""
"Rationale: Default function arguments in C++ are a tempting way to add an "
"argument to a function while maintaining easy backwards compatibility. "
"However, if you later want to add another argument to the list in a way that "
"preserves backwards compatibility, it, too, must be a default argument. To "
"supply the second of these arguments in a call forces you to also supply the "
"first argument, even if it is the default value. As a result, this is not a "
"clean way to add a argument to a function. Instead, function overloading "
"should be preferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:190
msgid ""
"VTK classes (header and source file) must be defined in the "
"VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE, using VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_BEGIN and VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_END "
"at the deepest namespace level, if any."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:191
msgid ""
"VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_BEGIN\n"
"class VTKXXX_EXPORT vtkXXX : public vtkObject{/* ... */};\n"
"VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_END\n"
"\n"
"namespace vtk {\n"
"VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_BEGIN\n"
"void VTKXXX_EXPORT yyy();\n"
"VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_END\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:203
msgid ""
"Removing of public and even protected members and methods should follow "
"[deprecation policy](./git/deprecation.md#deprecation-policy)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:205
msgid "Rationale: Consistent API,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:207
msgid ""
"Fully unused arguments in functions and methods should not be omitted but "
"instead should be hidden using `vtkNotUsed(arg)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:211
msgid "Specific C++  Language Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:212
msgid "C++ Standard Library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:214
msgid "Do not use vtkStdString in new API; prefer std::string"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:216
msgid ""
"Rationale: vtkStdString was introduced as a workaround for compilers that "
"couldn’t handle the long symbol name for the expanded std::string type. It "
"is no longer needed on modern platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:218
msgid ""
"STL usage in the Common modules' public API is discouraged when possible, "
"Common modules are free to use STL in  implementation files. The other "
"modules may use STL, but should do so only when necessary if there is not an "
"appropriate VTK class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:220
msgid ""
"Rationale: limits header inclusion bloat, wrappers are not capable of "
"handling many non-`vtkObject` derived classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:222
msgid "C++ Language Features Required when using VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:224
msgid ""
"[*nullptr*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/nullptr) Use `nullptr` "
"instead of `0` and `NULL` when dealing with pointer types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:225
msgid ""
"[*override*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/override)  "
"`VTK_OVERRIDE` will be replaced with the override keyword"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:226
msgid ""
"[*final*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/final)  `VTK_FINAL` will "
"be replaced with the final keyword"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:227
msgid ""
"[*delete*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"function#Deleted_functions) The use of delete is preferred over making "
"default members private and unimplemented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:228
msgid ""
"[*non static data member initializers*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/"
"language/data_members)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:230
msgid "C++ Features allowed throughout VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:232
msgid ""
"[*default*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/default_constructor)  "
"The use of default is encouraged in preference to empty destructor "
"implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:233
msgid ""
"[*static_assert*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/static_assert) "
"Must use the static_assert ( `bool_constexpr` ) signature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:234
msgid ""
"[*strongly typed enums*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/enum) VTK "
"prefers the usage of strongly typed enums over classic weakly typed enums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:238
msgid ""
"Weakly typed enums conversion to integers is undesirable, and the ability "
"for strongly typed enums to specify explicit storage size make it the "
"preferred form of enums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:242
msgid "strongly typed: `enum class Color { red, blue };`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:244
msgid "weakly typed: `enum Color { red, blue };`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:246
msgid ""
"While VTK is aware that conversion of all enums over to strongly typed enums "
"will uncover a collection of subtle faults and incorrect assumptions. "
"Converting existing classes to use strongly typed enums will need to be "
"investigated and discussed with the mailing list, as this will break API/"
"ABI, potentially cause issues with VTK bindings, and possibly require "
"changes to users VTK code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:253
msgid ""
"[*attributes*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/attributes)  The "
"use of attribute is encouraged and should be used wisely depending on the "
"attribute:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:254
msgid ""
"[*fallthough*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/attributes/"
"fallthrough.html) should be used instead of `VTK_FALLTHROUGH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:255
msgid ""
"[*maybe_unused*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/attributes/"
"maybe_unused.html) should be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:256
msgid ""
"[*nodiscard*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/attributes/"
"nodiscard.html) should be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:258
msgid ""
"[*std::optional*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/optional.html) "
"should be used for returned value of method to simplify method signature and "
"to factorize code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:260
msgid ""
"[*std::string_view*](http://www.en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/header/string_view."
"html) should be used to avoid string copy especially for IO treatment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:262
msgid ""
"[*class template argument deduction*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/"
"language/class_template_argument_deduction.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:264
msgid ""
"Usage of class template argument deduction can be used for trivial type "
"deduction like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:265
msgid ""
"std::pair p(2, 4.5);     // deduces to std::pair<int, double> p(2, 4.5);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:269
msgid ""
"C++ Features acceptable in VTK implementation files, private headers, and "
"template implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:271
msgid ""
"[*braced initializer list*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"list_initialization)  Braced initializer list are allowed as they prevent "
"implicit narrowing conversions, and “most vexing parse” errors. They can be "
"used when constructing POD’s  and other containers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:274
msgid ""
"**Braced initializer lists are not allowed to be used as the right hand side "
"for auto:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:276
msgid ""
"  auto a = { 10, 20 }; //not allowed as a is std::initializer_list<int>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:280
msgid "[*shared_ptr*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/memory/shared_ptr)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:281
msgid ""
"**Do not combine shared_ptr and vtk derived objects.** VTK internal "
"reference counting makes the shared_ptr reference counting ( and destructor "
"tracking ) pointless."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:283
msgid ""
"[*template alias*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/type_alias)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:284
msgid ""
"The use of alias templates is preferred over using 'typedefs'. They provide "
"the same language pattern of normal declarations, and reduce the need for "
"helper template structs. For example ( Scott Meyers, Effective Modern C++ )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:286
msgid "template<typename T> using MyAllocList = std::list<T, MyAlloc<T>>;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:290
msgid "universal references (&&) / std::move / std::forward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:292
msgid ""
"[*extern templates*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"class_template)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:294
msgid "Used in the `vtkDataArray` for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:296
msgid ""
"[*unordered maps*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/"
"UnorderedAssociativeContainer)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:298
msgid "[*std::array* ](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/array)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:300
msgid ""
"The use of std::array is preferred over using raw fixed sized arrays. They "
"offer compile time bounds checking without any runtime cost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:302
msgid ""
"[*range based for loop*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/range-for)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:304
msgid ""
"[*std::variant*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/variant.html) can "
"be used in internal API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:306
msgid "C++ Features allowed under certain conditions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:308
msgid "[*concurrency*](https://isocpp.org/wiki/faq/cpp11-library-concurrency)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:310
msgid ""
"Concurrency inside of vtk should be handled by using or extending the "
"already existing collection of support classes like vtkAtomic and "
"vtkSMPThreadLocal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:312
msgid ""
"Instead of directly using new c++11 constructs such as std::"
"compare_exchange_weak instead extend the functionality of vtk core "
"concurrency classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:314
msgid ""
"Note: Thread local storage has not been supported on OSX previously to XCode "
"8. VTK offers the following classes that should be used instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:316
msgid ""
"[vtkSMPThreadLocalObject](http://www.vtk.org/doc/release/7.0/html/"
"classvtkSMPThreadLocalObject.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:318
msgid ""
"[vtkSMPThreadLocal](http://www.vtk.org/doc/release/6.3/html/"
"classvtkSMPThreadLocal.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:320
msgid ""
"[*std::isnan*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/numeric/math/isnan), [*std::"
"isfinite*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/numeric/math/isfinite), [*std::"
"isinf*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/numeric/math/isinf)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:322
msgid ""
"These functions should not be called directly,  instead the wrapped versions "
"provided by vtk should be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:324
msgid "vtk::isnan -> std::isnan"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:326
msgid "vtk::isfinite -> std::isfinite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:328
msgid "vtk::isisinfnan -> std::isinf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:330
msgid ""
"The reason for these wrappings is to work around compiler performance "
"issues. For example,  some clang version would convert integral types to "
"double and do the operation on the double value, instead of simply returning "
"false/true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:332
msgid ""
"[*std::future*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/thread/future)/ [*std::"
"async*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/thread/async)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:334
msgid ""
"Future/Async based programming inside of vtk should be handled on a case by "
"case basis. In general the use cases for this kind of execution model is "
"best applied at the vtkExecutive / vtkPipeline level, or at the File IO "
"level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:336
msgid ""
"In these cases the recommendation is to extending or adding support classes "
"so that these design patterns can be utilized in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:338
msgid ""
"[*constexpr*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/constexpr.html) "
"should be used for constant (instead of `#define`, `const ...`) and wisely "
"used for function depending on your use case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:340
msgid ""
"[*auto*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/auto) Use auto to avoid "
"type names that are noisy, obvious, or unimportant - cases where the type "
"doesn't aid in clarity for the reader. auto is permitted when it increases "
"readability, particularly as described below. **Never initialize an auto-"
"typed variable with a braced initializer list.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:344
msgid "Specific cases where auto is allowed or encouraged:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:345
msgid ""
"(Encouraged) For iterators and other long/convoluted type names, "
"particularly when the type is clear from context (calls to find, begin, or "
"end for instance)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:346
msgid ""
"(Allowed) When the type is clear from local context (in the same expression "
"or within a few lines). Initialization of a pointer or smart pointer with "
"calls to new commonly falls into this category, as does use of auto in a "
"range-based loop over a container whose type is spelled out nearby."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:347
msgid ""
"(Allowed) When the type doesn't matter because it isn't being used for "
"anything other than equality comparison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:348
msgid ""
"(Encouraged) When iterating over a map with a range-based loop (because it "
"is often assumed that the correct type is std::pair<KeyType, ValueType> "
"whereas it is actually std::pair<const KeyType, ValueType>). This is "
"particularly well paired with local key and value aliases for .first and ."
"second (often const-ref)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:349
msgid ""
"for (const auto& [key, value] : some_map) {\n"
"// The rest of the loop can now just refer to key and value,\n"
"// a reader can see the types in question, and we've avoided\n"
"// the too-common case of extra copies in this iteration.\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:356
msgid ""
"(Allowed) [structure binding](https://cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"structured_binding.html) can be used for trivial type deduction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:357
msgid ""
"(Prohibited) When iterating in integer space. `for (auto i=0; i < grid-"
">GetNumberOfPoints(); ++i)`. Because vtk data structures usually contain "
"more than 2 billion elements, iterating using 32bit integer is prohibited in "
"these use case (and often doesn’t match the type used)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:359
msgid "[*unique_ptr*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/memory/unique_ptr)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:360
msgid ""
"Do not use unique_ptr with vtk-derived objects. We recommend using `vtkNew` "
"because VTK objects have their own internal reference counting and custom "
"deletion logic, making unique_ptr's ownership semantics invalid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:361
msgid "`std::unique_ptr` should be created with `make_unique`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:363
msgid ""
"[*lambda expressions*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/lambda)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:365
msgid "Usage of lambda expressions are allowed with the following guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:367
msgid ""
"Use default capture by value ([=]) only as a means of binding a few "
"variables for a short lambda, where the set of captured variables is obvious "
"at a glance. Prefer not to write long or complex lambdas with default "
"capture by value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:368
msgid ""
"All capture arguments must be explicitly defined. Using the default capture "
"by reference ([&]) is not permitted. This ensures easier evaluation of "
"lifespan and reference ownership."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:369
msgid "lambda expression should be `constexpr`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:370
msgid ""
"Keep unnamed lambdas short. If a lambda body is more than maybe five lines "
"long, prefer using a named function instead of a lambda."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:371
msgid ""
"Specify the return type of the lambda explicitly if that will make it more "
"obvious to readers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:373
msgid ""
"[*variadic templates*](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"parameter_pack) and [*fold expression*](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/"
"language/fold.html)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:375
msgid ""
"Variadic Templates and fold expression are not allowed in VTK unless they "
"are the only solution to the given problem (e.g. `vtkArrayDispatch.txx`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:377
msgid "VTK’s commit hook enforced style checks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:379
msgid "Well formed commit message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:381
msgid ""
"Every commit message should consist of a one line summary optionally "
"followed by a blank line and further details. This is most easily "
"approximated to the subject of an email, and the body in the form of "
"paragraphs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:383
msgid ""
"Valid committer username and email address Every developer must have a valid "
"name and email configured in git.\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:386
msgid "ASCII filename check All file names must contain only ASCII characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:389
msgid "No tabs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:391
msgid "No trailing whitespace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:393
msgid "No empty line at end of file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:395
msgid "Proper file access mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:397
msgid "Files must be committed with sensible access modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:399
msgid "One megabyte maximum file size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:401
msgid "No submodules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:403
msgid ""
"For required third party dependencies, the recommended scheme is to use "
"git's subtree merge strategy to reproducibly import code and thereby "
"simplify eventual integration of upstream changes. Copies of these third "
"party libraries with branches specifically for vendoring them in VTK are "
"located in the [third-party](https://gitlab.kitware.com/third-party/) GitLab "
"space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/coding_conventions.md:405
msgid ""
"Additionally, new developers should be aware that the regression test "
"machines have fairly strict compiler warnings enabled and usually have "
"VTK_DEBUG_LEAKS configured on to catch leaks of VTK objects. Developers "
"should be in the habit of doing the same in their own environments so as to "
"avoid pushing code that the dashboards will immediately object to. With GCC, "
"it is easiest to do so by turning on VTK_EXTRA_COMPILER_WARNINGS."
msgstr ""
